==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spiccato
<hw>Spic*ca"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[It., p. p. of
<ets>spicare</ets> to detach, to separate.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>Detached; separated; -- a term indicating that every note is to be
performed in a distinct and pointed manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spice</ent>⟦br⟧
